metadata.name: Futuristic Trees
metadata.description:
Futuristic trees is a generative collection of trees in a dystopian world in the year 2099.
In that year there are few humans left living in colonies. The trees are made of titanium, carbon fiber and graphene to resist climatic conditions such as toxic gases and radioactive rains, they work with electric energy and their function is to produce oxygen for the colonies.

Futuristic trees have :
19 types of trees.
2 seasons, summer and winter.
2 types of rain, normal and radioactive. 
It also has snow and 20 types of backgrounds.
If you are lucky you can get GOLD or SILVER TREE!!!

Please note that the algorithm can take some time to run.
Press "S" in live mode to save image 1500x1500.

Created by Fernando. NFT License 2.0.

metadata.name: Los Generators - Enter The Machine
metadata.description:
From Spain we present our FxHash Genesis, a layered png generative artwork:

Los Generators - Enter The Machine
"100 years ago, a family of inventors trying to break into the metaverse, its 2022 and they made it."

The post-folk band is a rare gem, working tirelessly to get this album to web3, set like clockwork the family of Spanish musician-inventors ensures that their effort was not in vain.

Enter The Machine is a concept album, chronicling the inventiveness of an isolated family, creating trinkets and instruments that would make it possible for their album to be encrypted in 1922 and only surface in 2022, where its unique content can be enjoyed.

Los Generators invite you to discover their universe, presented through several randomized album covers, with different graphics and characters, with more than 900 combination possibilities.

Can you imagine their music?

The code part was created using the P5 library to make the combinations between the ready-made layers and manipulate the pixels, placing the layers overlay on a canvas in the html and creating a noise filter using the 'loadPixel()' function.
A simple function was made to save the canvas when pressing the 'P' key, saving a png in 1000x1000p resolution.

Album cover condition: various.
1000x1000 pixels, PNG, 32 bit.
Metabandz and nt_worm, 2022.

Metabandz is a label presenting album cover nft's for fictional music bands.

metadata.name: Brushroom
metadata.description:
Several generative systems combine to paint this whimsical nature scene.  Each iteration is constructed with a coin-flip chance of implementing the various generative systems:

-> Three Background Styles
-> Hedges Form
-> Grass Form
-> Stones and Pebbles Form

A randomized color palette is coordinated among all the systems to
achieve an homogenous color-effect.  The mushroom forms are colored using noise and stochastic selection.  The proportions are randomized, as well.

metadata.name: Phantom Mask
metadata.description:
Multidimensional apparitions via mathematical geometric structures in the blockchain.
Figurative representational tradition meets code pattern ordering as dream-like robot heads. The tradition of face mask making and representation in modern art in dialogue with the ever changing all-possible computer programs and always present unforeseen glitch errors.
As a meta-language, the computer reads and mixes human and android facial features, as the automatic creation mimics its creator.
The robot generative portraits are a looking glass into the source code of the artwork.
Touch to voice the void of the hash.

Alexandre Rangel, 2022
www.alexandrerangel.art.br

metadata.name: Riptide
metadata.description:
Riptide is a project using independent layered 2D Perlin noises to generate a wide variety of images.

Each noise map controls one or multiple parameters of the piece (grid position, group of lines orientation, spread, color, opacity ...). A final modifier is then applied on top of it to change the amount of effect each parameter has on every group of lines.

Learn more on how Riptide works at: https://estienne.ca/riptide


CONTROLS:
Press [S] to save a 3000 x 3000 pixels png image (for other resolutions, check the editor)
Press [T] to toggle between light mode and dark mode
Press [B] to toggle the tilt-shift blur effect

EDITOR:
Press [H] or double-tap to toggle the Riptide Editor.
This menu allows you to play with the Riptide algorithm. You can modify your edition or create a brand new Riptide with the parameters of your choice.
This menu also gives you the possibility to save an image in any resolution (depending of your configuration). However, for images bigger than 4000 x 4000 pixels, it is recommended to turn off the blur effect to avoid unexpected results.

This project has been tested on Chrome Version 98.0.4758.102

Artist: Estienne
Licence:
- Minted image with untouched parameters: NFT 2.0
- Images produced by the editor with custom parameters: Personal use only


IMPORTANT: The publication of this series is done via a manually updated Dutch auction:
Opening at 12 tez
10 tez after 15 minutes
8 tez after 30 minutes
6 tez for the remaining editions

metadata.name: Primes
metadata.description:
This piece displays the first 1000 primes in polar coordinates. It then selects 10% of them. Exactly which ones is decided by the hash, creating unique pieces every time. 
4 markers types are used to display your unique version, in decreasing order of probability: squares, pentagons, hexagons, circles. The banner at the bottom displays the sum of the selected primes.

metadata.name: Glimpse Of Draeconian Epidermis & Tapestry
metadata.description:
Discover the artistic style and bold fashion of your favorite Reptilian overlords, the *Draeconians*!

Those NFTs are pictures, sure, but more intricately they are *Glimpses* of what these magnificent scaled shapeshifters are able to create using their sophisticated *Epidermis* machinery.

Nevertheless, and as it is the case for some humans in our world, you'll probably notice eventually that more often than not, the output products are better suited to be used as *Tapestry* rather than clothes or skin...

Features:
- 42 palettes aka Pigmentore's Names
- 4 rendering techniques aka Workore's Names
- 5 types of patterns aka Designore's Tribes...
- ... which result into more than 40 different patterns aka Designore's Names
- 5 transformations aka Designore's Traits
- etc.

About me:
I am MaKRz, a creative coder and generative artist living in Lisbon area. I like to take inspiration in real life and nature (animals, landscapes, buildings) to start with a concept and eventually totally mess it up.
Check out @MaKRz666 on Twitter.

Made with p5js

metadata.name: Oh, Very Funny
metadata.description:
Ever heard a joke that made you literally face palm?
Ever had a friend that just couldn't take the hint that their jokes suck?

This is a collection of situations exactly like that, presented as text message exchanges.

Features:
12 different phone models (with rarity!)
Over 200 horrible, cringe-worthy jokes
Over 100 quippy comebacks from the joke victim
Random values for network signal, battery charge, carrier name, contact name, and current time

metadata.name: Twilight Canyon
metadata.description:
Adrift like shadows under the twilight moon, we wait for the arrival of the eschaton.

What forbidden worlds will we find there? 

As celestial bodies prove ominous omens under a gradient sky, we ask ourselves, "Have we died in this strange landscape? Or have we only just learned to live?"

Features:
Moons
Comets
Monolith
Clouds

metadata.description:

All art sold is dedicated to the men and women who served the US Military. Proceeds go to support veterans and their families.

metadata.name: Apparitions
metadata.description:
There have always been apparitions. 
Hovering above the surface of the paper. 
Shadowing the charcoal markings. 
Living alongside us in our world. 

This piece is dedicated to transcendental collision of a drawing implement and its receptive canvas. Patience is required, since the apparitions may take some time to materialize.

metadata.name: Liiiiights
metadata.description:
"Memory can change the shape of a room, the colour of a car; and memories can be distorted. They're just an interpretation; they're not a record.”
Leonard Shelby, Memento


This project uses only straight lines to create abstract compositions that evoke memories/dreams of stage lights, live music shows, raves and dance clubs. Most outputs are bright, vibrant and chaotic, some are more even and intricately geometric, and a few will have quiet, subtle minimalist compositions.

The (mis)spelling of Liiiiights is a reference to the nested loops used to create the recurring lines. Also as I was developing this algorithm and trying to steer the outputs to be more “stage lighty” I began to prefer the ones that had glitches, odd geometry, repeating patterns, too many layers or other imperfections in them, and so I started embracing those elements and incorporating them. Some outputs also have a texture similar to that of a page from an old photocopier, which I’ve seen used as a metaphor for how memories work in our brains: that the process of recalling a memory is akin to taking a photo out from a file, making a photocopy of it and putting that copy back in your memory file, so that each time you access it, it loses a little bit of fidelity and eventually becomes a foggy distorted facsimile of the original memory. 

I hope Liiiiights sparks positive memories for you, regardless of how fuzzy, or at least gives you good vibes and provides a place for your eyes to dance around.

Twitter.com/fauxjebus
Instagram.com/fauxjebus

metadata.name: Broken Patterns Resolve
metadata.description: I derived this work from generative visual experiments I created way back in 2012. I was trying to make a Spirograph, also known as a Hypotrochoid if you're a mathy. I like the results of this broken code tangent more than the working version, and I revisited it from time to time. It's always special to pull a project out of the dustbin and make it dance again. Enjoy!

metadata.name: I AM THAT I AM
metadata.description:
this is a generative piece inspired by the poem "I Am That I Am", by Brion Gysin and the brownian motion. 
two references that i belive are very important to the actual generative art. 

they walked so we can run

on youtube u can find an audio made by brion, where he declaim all the possibilities of this poem.
